President Obama dropped by a meeting between National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice and outgoing Secretary-General of the United Nations Ban Ki-moon. The President thanked Ban for his leadership of the United Nations and they discussed the accomplishments made by the United States and the United Nations since 2009. These accomplishments include strengthening international action on climate change, armed conflicts, human rights, economic development, inequality, and addressing the nuclear and missile activities of Iran and North Korea. President Obama emphasized the importance of a strong partnership between the United States and the United Nations and urged continued efforts to reform and strengthen the organization to address the demands for international action.